functionDecorators.name: isApprovedForAll
functionDecorators.description: Query if an address is an authorized operator for another address.

parameterDecorators.name: _recordOwner
parameterDecorators.description: The address that owns the records.

parameterDecorators.name: _operator
parameterDecorators.description: The address that acts on behalf of the owner.

returnDecorators.description: True if `operator` is an approved operator for `owner`, false otherwise.

functionDecorators.name: owner
functionDecorators.description: Returns the address that owns the specified node.

functionDecorators.name: owner
functionDecorators.description: Returns the address of the current owner.

functionDecorators.name: recordExists
functionDecorators.description: Returns whether a record has been imported to the registry.

functionDecorators.name: renounceOwnership
functionDecorators.description: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

functionDecorators.name: resolver
functionDecorators.description: Returns the address of the resolver for the specified node.

functionDecorators.name: setApprovalForAll
functionDecorators.description: Enable or disable approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of `msg.sender`'s ENS records. Emits the ApprovalForAll event.

parameterDecorators.name: _operator
parameterDecorators.description: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.

parameterDecorators.name: _approved
parameterDecorators.description: True if the operator is approved, false to revoke approval.

functionDecorators.name: setOwner
functionDecorators.description: Transfers ownership of a node to a new address. May only be called by the current owner of the node.

parameterDecorators.name: _node
parameterDecorators.description: The node to transfer ownership of.

parameterDecorators.name: _recordOwner
parameterDecorators.description: The address of the new owner.

functionDecorators.name: setRecord
functionDecorators.description: Sets the record for a node.

parameterDecorators.name: _recordOwner
parameterDecorators.description: The address of the new owner.

functionDecorators.name: setResolver
functionDecorators.description: Sets the resolver address for the specified node.

functionDecorators.name: setSubnodeOwner
functionDecorators.description: Transfers ownership of a subnode keccak256(node, label) to a new address. May only be called by the owner of the parent node.

parameterDecorators.name: _label
parameterDecorators.description: The hash of the label specifying the subnode.

parameterDecorators.name: _recordOwner
parameterDecorators.description: The address of the new owner.

functionDecorators.name: setSubnodeRecord
functionDecorators.description: Sets the record for a subnode.

parameterDecorators.name: _label
parameterDecorators.description: The hash of the label specifying the subnode.

parameterDecorators.name: _recordOwner
parameterDecorators.description: The address of the new owner.

functionDecorators.name: setTTL
functionDecorators.description: Sets the TTL for the specified node.

functionDecorators.name: transferOwnership
functionDecorators.description: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

functionDecorators.name: ttl
functionDecorators.description: Returns the TTL of a node, and any records associated with it.

functionDecorators.name: upgradeTo
functionDecorators.description: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

functionDecorators.name: upgradeToAndCall
functionDecorators.description: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.
